  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: chat jumps to several rows in the case when the edge of message and edge of input area are overlapping. Same behavior when scrolling to start of day history (to \"Today\" label for instance)\r\n![scro](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/45949606-184eff80-c005-11e8-88d7-a066f04e1317.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nno autoscrolling\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nautoscrolling to several rows or the middle of the previous message\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open any public chat \r\n- Scroll slowly to the edge of the last message\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: status desktop 24/09/18\r\n* Operating System: Mac OSx\r\n* Video: http://take.ms/3xE2V\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://api.monosnap.com/rpc/file/download?id=3sEGptrqYh3C6xxLFAg3dT60nouDO9&type=preview\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div>Monosnap screenshot tool</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://monosnap.com/file/3sEGptrqYh3C6xxLFAg3dT60nouDO9\">File \"screencast 2018-09-24 14-25-50.mp4\"</a></strong></div><div>Monosnap — the best tool to take & share your screenshots.</div></blockquote>",
